cable.user_prompt:
Analyze this coaxial cable datasheet and extract the following specifications. Return ONLY a JSON object with these fields:

{
  "component_type": "cable",
  "manufacturer": "<manufacturer name>",
  "model": "<model number>",
  "part_number": "<part number if different from model>",
  "description": "<brief description including diameter and type>",
  "impedance_ohms": <50 or 75>,
  "velocity_factor": <decimal value 0.60-0.95>,
  "outer_diameter_inches": <diameter in inches>,
  "loss_db_per_100ft": {
    "<freq_mhz>": <loss value>,
    // Include all frequencies listed in datasheet
  },
  "power_rating_watts": {
    "<freq_mhz>_mhz": <power in watts>,
    // Include all frequencies listed
  },
  "weight_lbs_per_100ft": <weight>,
  "minimum_bend_radius_inches": <bend radius>,
  "datasheet_url": "<URL if mentioned in document>",
  "common_uses": ["<use 1>", "<use 2>"],
  "notes": "<any important notes about this cable>"
}

If a field is not found in the datasheet, use null. Be precise with numeric values. Extract ALL frequency points for loss and power ratings.
